				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">NTSC NES always draws 256x240. PAL NES draws 252x239.<br /><br />SNES can either draw 256x224, or 256x239, depending on what the game requests. So most games use the mode with lower vertical resolution, and those extra 15 missing scanlines are why it looks letterboxed.<br /><br />You should be able to use your TV's service menu to stretch things out vertically.</div>

